iff.\nKendall IF Perkins\nWill S. Fawcett\nSam Robinson\nChas. E. Anderson\nEarl Richmond\nF. B. Johnson\nJohn Zurcher\nFrank Richmond\nRay Johnson\nJ. I). Adams\nChas. E. Farrell\nBen H. Hulse\nWalter F. Sebley\nI. A. Thomas\nPaul Pace\nS. P. Williams\nJosh L. Wilson\nMarcia Farrell\nJ. C. Sharp\nRoy Breedlove\nW. 0. Hendricks\nHarold A. Burnham\nWATCH THIS SPACE TOMORROW\nEmery Girard\nRalph Swearingen\nS. L. McCrory\nMark Washburn\nFlorence Allenby\nLois K. Anderson\nH. L. (Joe) Bush\nI)]-. N. E. Dupont\n0. J. Bradshaw\nMrs. O. J. Bradshaw\nHoward P. Meyer\nWarren Currier\nChas. Pitzer\nDon Bitler\nRoger S. Sumner\nL. C. Liebert\nJ. J. Green\nEarl Waugh\nRalph Therrien\nGuy Holmes\nMrs. Merta Thompson\nW. M. Wilson\nHubert C. House\nD. V. Stewart\nThis ndvertiacmcnt inserted and\nJohn Schmidt\nChas. A. Burke\nGeorge P. Fleming\nJ. Penmen\nC. E. Sonnenburg\nC. C. Proctor\nMattie P. Stewart\nWalter Blesy\nJohn T. Rice\nH. D. Deavers\nH. E. Holt\nSam Sears\nChas. Thatcher\nJohn Kuhn\nMrs. Harold Nichols\nRuth T. Wilson\nC. R. Chambers\nMrs. John Kuhn\nJ. W. Glasgow\nThad McCall\nHarold Nichols\nEloise McCall\nH. L. Stevens\nC. V. Smith\npaid for by local Pulliam supporters.\nNEW EVIDENCE\nIN MOONEY CASE\nPUZZLES JUDGE?\nSAN FRANCISCO, Oct. :0. (U.R)\nJust ires of tin* California supreme\ncourt today hold conflicting views 1\nconcerning the charges revealed j\nyesterday that William V. Mac- j\nVeviii, foreman of the jury during\nthe Tom Moonov trial, was in eon- r\nstunt consultation with the prnsecu-\nlion at the time.\nMooney, convicted with Warren\nK. Hillings of perpetrating tin- lttlti\nSan Francisco Preparedness day I\nI'omliing in which 10 persons were\nkilled, is serving a life term in San\n(Quentin prison.\nThe liitest charges, Chief Justice!\nWilliam H. Waste revealed, were\nmade t v .1. 11. Zimdars, attorney, t\nwho claimed that Mae Nevin had ad\ninitted complicity to him. Zirrdar\nal'-o submitted, when he appeared J\nefore ~ix justices of the con; t last\